                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370403-name-423" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-423" type="surname" value="BAILIFF"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-423" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD BAILIFF</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Queen-street, Hoxton, and am a hat manufacturer. The prisoner was in my employ about one year—on the 23rd of January, about two o'clock, I gave him eighteen sovereigns, eight half-sovereigns, and a£5 note, to take to the London and Westminster Bank, in Throgmorton-street—I saw no more of him till the 4th of March, when he was brought to me by an officer—the money has not been cre<lb></lb>dited to my account at the Bank—he had the pass-book, and took it away—I saw no more of it.</p>
